<div id="review_1701477225" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1701477225" />
    <a title="Lev Keltner" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/57736365-lev-keltner"><img alt="Lev Keltner" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1624480525p2/57736365.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1701477225?book_show_action=true">Apr 18, 2020</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Lev Keltner" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Lev Keltner" href="/user/show/57736365-lev-keltner">Lev Keltner</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1701477225" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer9889735818017536697">One of the best books from one of the best minds. This collection of speeches, theory, books, and interviews with Dr. King highlights his understanding of the relationship between inequities and social systems that require radical change, not on the grounds of ideology, but moral purpose, which to King means an ethics of love. A call to action and a profound legacy preserved.</span>

          </span>
        </div>


